title: Ulrika Eleonora, Queen of Sweden
summary: Ulrika Eleonora or Ulrica Eleanor (23 January 1688 â€“ 24 November 1741), known as Ulrika Eleonora the Younger, was Queen of Sweden, reigning in her own right from 5 December 1718 until her abdication on 29 February 1720 in favour of her husband King Frederick, and then as his consort until her death.
